RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 3 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Louisiana Bred NW2 $5000 & NW3 $5000 Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLUSHINSTREETDEVIL broke in and brushed a foe at the start, straightened momentarily before being asked to cross over while clearing, yet caused slight hinderance to a group of foes behind him while doing so, showed the way with a clear margin around the turn, and held sway from a chasing rival under driving pressure. STEALING APRIORITY bumped with rivals on both sides soon after the start, then brushed an inner foe when herded down by an outer rival in the early stages, chased the clear leader from the two path, but failed to progress through the lane while hanging on his left lead, and was second best. CREME DE BALI was bumped by an inner rival into an outer foe at the start, then got put to crowded quarters among those foes a few strides later, pursued from midpack, tucked to the inside entering the turn, shifted out three wide entering the lane, but only managed to chase while hanging on his left lead into the final furlong, changed over leaving that station, and held show. GENIUS was bumped by an inner rival into an outer foe at the start, brushed with those foes in the incident soon after, tracked along the inside under snug restraint, but was wrangled back to shift out nearing the turn, tipped four wide at the three furlong pole, then lacked a bid through the lane while hanging on his left lead. SPEEDY G bumped with rivals on both sides soon after the start, raced at the rear in the two to three paths, and moved up. COURAGEOUS TIMMY leaned out a touch at the start, chased three wide, but faded through the lane while remaining on his left lead. AFIKOMAN broke out and bumped a foe at the start, then was keen when brushed to tight rail quarters by outer rivals in the early stages, saved ground off of the pace around the turn, but to no avail. DA GOLD ROOM took a brush from an outer rival before bumping with an inner foe soon after, raced far back in the four to five paths, and was outrun. THE RIDER OFSTEALING APRIORITY CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF BLUSHINSTREETDEVIL FOR INTERFERENCE IN THE OPENING STAGES, BUT THE OBJECTION WAS DISALLOWED BY THE STEWARDS.

GALAXY BUILDER was in the second tier along the backside, was widest in the turn and stopped in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 86. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE SEPTEMBER 3, 2022. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 3 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOYFRIEND MATERIAL raced forwardly in the three path, emerged from between horses to be the clear leader's main pursuer around the turn, chased that foe while unable to progress through upper stretch, yet inched closer nearing the final sixteenth as the leader tired, and gained an advantage approaching the wire. KNOCKALITTLELOUDER set the pace via a clear margin while a path off of the rail around the turn, held sway through midstretch, but began to tire entering the final sixteenth, and gave in late before saving place. MILTONTOWN laid off of the pace three wide and between horses, handled crowded quarters well leaving the half mile pole, gained four wide and between horses around the bend, then stayed on outside of foes after changing leads at the three sixteenths pole, but ran out of ground to reach place. MAINTAINANCE MATT pursued from midpack along the inside, faltered while buried inside of rivals into the turn, raced towards the rear around the bend, then sustained a rail chase through the lane, vied for show late, but got outfinished while altering course around traffic nearing the wire, and dead-heated for fourth. DREWZANO was last away while off a step slow, raced at the rear in the two path while tugging behind foes down the backstretch, moved between horses nearing the turn, knifed through three wide at the five sixteenths pole, but only managed to chase among foes through the lane while lacking a bid, then dead-heated for fourth. SUN SQUALL chased in the two path and lacked a bid. FRANK THE MAYOR chased five wide and outside of foes from midpack briefly, but retreated to trail the field entering the turn, and never got involved. COMPLEX SYSTEM tracked four wide, but faded in the six path around the turn.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALIBRACHOA KID was racing from the four path early, continued gaining ground from the outside through the turn, shifted in a bit in the lane was driven and kept to task while chasing the early leader, slightly drifted out and and was brought back in allowing CALIBRACHOA KID to switch leads again and lengthen his stride with less than ten strides left to go, he was able to catch the early leader and pass him for the win. AZTEC GEM sent for the lead, was able to attend to the pace for most of the race, looked like the winner until deep in the stretch where he was collared late with not enough time to battle back, but had done enough work to hold on to second. MALAKI EMPIRE was off slow, settled far off the pace early was asked and responded well, made one long run from the outside and closed well. MACHO BEANIE was in the second tier in the three path early, drifted down closer to the rail in the turn slightly brushing an inside rival, traveled along the rail in the lane but tired late. ZINGING BAYOU was racing in the second tier from the rail, shifted out in the turn, was four wide in the lane and tired while still one his left lead. OURPERFECTPRINCE was racing with determination from in between foes in the second tier down the backside, dropped over to the rail through the turn, was in tight briefly and hit the rail, regained his stride and closed in the lane before tiring. MADELYN'S SOLDIER never involved. THERER WAS A JOCKEY CLAIM OF FOUL. THE JOCKEY ON OURPERFECTPRINCE CALIMED FOUL AGAINST THE JOCKEY OF MACHO BEANIE FOR ALLEDGED INTERFERNCE IN THE SECOND TURN. AFTER A STEWART'S REVIEW NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOME VISIT dueled for the lead inside of a rival, then inside of a pair of foes around the far turn as an outer KINGOFBROKENHEARTS bid, got headed by that one entering the lane, fought on through midstretch, reclaimed an advantage in the final sixteenth, and lasted from an outer on-charging foe late. SUNDAY BREEZE broke a step slow while while bumping with an inner rival and brushing with an outer foe at the start, trailed in the three path, gained in the path around the far turn, fanned to the four path in upper stretch with multiple lengths to find on the top pair, surged outside of them in the closing stages, but narrowly came up short. KINGOFBROKENHEARTS laid off of the pace along the inside, improved with nine sixteenths to go to gain show before tipping three wide to stalk outside of the top pair, bid into the far turn, vied three wide around that bend, led entering the lane, but failed to kick on leaving the furlong grounds, lost the advantage to her inner counterpart in the final sixteenth, and was outkicked for place late. MARTINIZED stalked outside of the top pair, got floated four wide by an inner moving foe at the nine sixteenths pole, chased under urging around the far turn, and lacked a bid while hanging on his left lead. JEFFROW broke a beat slow while bumping an outer rival at the start, laid unhurried in the two path, took the far turn two wide, and failed to factor. FORTY THREE dueled for the lead two wide, then from between horses into the far turn, but gave way turning for home, and weakened through the lane. TOUCHDOWN JOE pursued from midpack four to five wide, but faded into the far turn. CALCULATED stumbled badly before propping at the start, pulled after shifting out to the three path around the first turn, tugged between horses nearing the backstretch, but steadied out from that spot entering it, then faded along the inside around the far turn.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: OH MY ACHING ARCH bumped with an inner rival at the start, then steadied while in tight quarters between horses approaching the wire for the first time, clipped heels with an inner rival in the aftermath, settled at the rear along the inside, shifted to the three path entering the lane, rallied between horses to bid inside of the leader in the final furlong, and edged an advantage late. FOUR SEVENS stalked in the three path, advanced to the fore entering the backstretch, cleared approaching the five furlong pole, showed the way along the inside around the far turn, shifted out to the three to four paths while resisting outer bids in upper stretch, but met a pair of inner bids leaving the furlong grounds, and got bested in the final sixteenth. COFFEE COUNTY bumped with rivals on both sides at the start, then shied from an inner rival causing him to clip heels with an outer foe nearing the wire for the first time, settled off of the pace in the two to three paths, fanned to the seven path entering the lane, and chased. JEB'S LUCKY EIGHT set the pace in the two path, but got headed by an outer rival entering the backstretch, stalked outside of that foe entering the far turn, but floated to the five path entering the lane, and yielded in upper stretch while hanging on his left lead.
